In this video, we will learn the following things - 
1. Modulus properties
2. Fermat theorem

10^9 + 7 is a prime number.
Why 10e9+7 ?

In C++, using long long int, we can store numbers till 10e18.
When we do a%b, we can get the answer from 0->b-1.

So for large answers, we are asked to use 10e9+7, ex: (100!) % 10e9+7.

Modulus Properties:
1) (a+b)%c = (a%c + b%c)%c
2) (axb)%c = (a%c x b%c)%c
3) (a-b)%c = (a - b + c)%c
4) (a/b)%c = (a%c + (b^(c-2))%c)%c if c is prime.
